al of reading twenty pages and I will read like this today, I will let myself relax and read as I want, I familiarized myself with the pronunciation of the French language a little bit and then I really wanted to. Hamlet's monologue in French greets me from there. What are you doing? Well, it went, it took half a day again to get it more or less somehow, somehow. Well, I don't know, I haven't dared to listen myself yet. A starter package for reading digital books is currently being developed, and a mobile app should be ready by mid-December. The app will definitely add more convenience functions, i.e. you can also leave bookmarks and conveniently rewind fifteen seconds or thirty seconds back if you need to listen to something. Sleep timers and all such comfort functions will come later, which will only make all this listening more pleasant. Ott Nool talks about the weather of the new week. Good evening. It will gradually get cooler outside, because tomorrow the high pressure will have a big say along the Baltic Sea, the center of which will be over Poland, and along the edge of the high pressure, colder air will arrive in the Baltic countries and Finland in the north-west wind, which is why the thermometer readings will drop to minus in the inland areas during the coming night, and there will be a risk of slippery conditions on the roads. Tomorrow day, this high-pressure edge will be used by a low-pressure depression that comes from Finland and crosses to the southeast of Estonia, bringing light rain to Northern Estonia. On Tuesday, the low pressure area will move away to Russia, and the high pressure will cover the Baltic Sea countries. However, there is also humidity around here, and typical of autumn, high pressure does not always mean sunshine. Cloudiness is intermittent at night and it rains at times in the coastal areas. The wind from the west blows from two to seven, on the coast the gust was eleven meters per second. The air temperature is minus two to plus 